The paper focuses on visualizing and understanding Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) at the unit-, object-, and scene-level, which involves computer vision (CV) and machine learning (ML) techniques. Therefore, cs.CV and cs.LG are the most likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the architectural choices and improvements in GANs, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (AI) and neural networks (NE). Finally, the paper also mentions the segmentation-based network dissection method, which is related to computer graphics (GR).
